<span id="freeTextContainer4467448445538197115">I ended up reading the whole book (520+ pages) while traveling. I started the book while waiting for the first flights, and finished just when arriving at the destination. This, I think, was my first Robert Ludlum (that at least I can think of), and was a very enjoyable one to read too. The action starts at the first page, and finishes on the last. This is just perfect for the type of book - where you have the good and the bad guys, and need action and surprises. Very enjoyable, Ludlum definitel</span>
  <span id="freeText4467448445538197115" style="display:none">I ended up reading the whole book (520+ pages) while traveling. I started the book while waiting for the first flights, and finished just when arriving at the destination. This, I think, was my first Robert Ludlum (that at least I can think of), and was a very enjoyable one to read too. The action starts at the first page, and finishes on the last. This is just perfect for the type of book - where you have the good and the bad guys, and need action and surprises. Very enjoyable, Ludlum definitely masters the style. <br /><br />I love many of Ludlum's books, and this is definitely among my favorites. Lots and lots of action. Cold war still on. Lots of exotic places. </span>
